<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-18T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-18T09:00:00-05:00" n="493" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d493">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">585.61B1/583: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-18T16:00:00+02:00">July
                                        18, 1941—4 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received July 19—8:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3084. Department’s 2661, 18th.<note n="32" xml:id="d493fn32">Not
                                    printed.</note> Foreign Office stated orally this morning that
                                British authorities concerned do not believe it technically possible
                                to obtain assent of contracting parties because the majority are
                                either enemies or unaccessible governments. They will forward
                                shortly an alternative proposal not to enforce the convention
                                between ourselves.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>